HUMAN remains have been discovered on a waste ground near an industrial estate.
It is understood the remains were found by workmen digging at the site on Dale Avenue, near the old Hoover factory, Cambuslang on Tuesday.
Police Scotland were today unable to confirm if the remains belong to man or a woman.
There were also no details of what was found or how long it may have been at the scene.
A force spokesman said: “ Police Scotland can confirm that inquires are underway following the discovery of human remains found at Dale Avenue, Cambuslang on Tuesday April 7.
“Forensic examination of the remains will be carried out.
“A search of the area is currently underway.
“Officers are conducting inquires to establish the identity and circumstances and surrounding the discovery.”
